Package: zernel-cli
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: python3 (>= 3.10), zerneld
Description: Zernel CLI IDE — terminal-native ML developer environment
 Terminal-native experiment tracking, model registry, job orchestration,
 live GPU dashboard, and ZQL query language for ML/LLM workloads.
 .
 Commands: zernel init, run, watch, exp, model, job, doctor, query.

Package: zerneld
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: zernel-cli, zernel-scheduler
Description: Zernel eBPF observability daemon
 Real-time ML workload observability via eBPF probes. Instruments GPU
 memory, CUDA kernel latency, NCCL collectives, and DataLoader I/O
 without any application code changes.
 .
 Exposes Prometheus metrics and WebSocket telemetry stream.

Package: zernel-scheduler
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, zerneld
Description: Zernel sched_ext ML-aware CPU scheduler
 Custom Linux CPU scheduler using sched_ext (Linux 6.12+) that detects
 ML workload phases (DataLoading, GpuCompute, NcclCollective,
 OptimizerStep) and applies phase-specific scheduling policies.
 .
 Features NUMA-aware CPU selection and multi-tenant GPU-proportional
 CPU allocation.
